text: Jennifer Hinze (born 20 May 1988) is a Canadian volleyball player. She is part of the Canadian women's national volleyball team. She competed at the 2009 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup, 2010 Women's Pan-American Volleyball Cup, 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, and 2011 Women's NORCECA Volleyball Championship. She played for University of British Columbia's women's volleyball team. == References == Category:1988 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian volleyball players Category:University of British Columbia alumni
